Description: SUPPLY CHAINS is a publication devoted to trends and opportunities in old-economy transportation and new-economy technology
Full Description: SUPPLY CHAINS: the place where old-economy transportation meets new-economy technology. In 1869, Leland Stanford drove the Golden Spike into the ground in Utah, creating the first coast-to-coast railroad. The railroads supported billion-dollar modern-dollar fortunes for owners like the Vanderbilts, Carnegies and Flaglers. One century later, in 1956 Malcolm McLean invented containerization, enabling not just modern steamships but also global retail powerhouses like Walmart. Today, we have entered the third wave of value creation. Instead of railroads and steamships, the new-economy supply chain leaders have learned how to harness the power of technology. SUPPLY CHAINS explores this intersection, evaluates the trends, and looks into the future. SUPPLY CHAINS is affiliated with Cambridge Capital, a leading investor in transportation, logistics, and supply chain technology. SUPPLY CHAINS is founded and edited by Benjamin Gordon. Benjamin Gordon has founded several companies in transportation and logistics, and has invested in many supply chain firms as well.

Description: Managerie's anonymized platform specializes in connecting growth-oriented individuals with organizations in need of cultural champions.
Full Description: We started Managerie to give people the space to articulate how they're trying to drive their career, and encourage companies to engage in that narrative. We've found an important first step is to lead with the information that highlights a forward-looking career trajectory, and help companies focus on the elements that contribute to actual success in a role. That's why at Managerie we prefer to highlight people's growth orientation, motivators, and best suited work environments, in addition to skills / qualifications and in return, companies are getting a full and honest picture of the human being they'd potentially be hiring. Our currency at Managerie is authenticity. We've designed a process that gets to the core of people's personal drivers and ambitions for their career by making intentional space for a genuine conversation with every candidate. Our primary aim is to get an honest and authentic picture of our candidates and what they need to perform at their best.
